    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 66 (Thursday, April 20, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Ms. NORTON:H.R. 2775.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Clause 18 of section 8 of Article I of the Constitution.The single subject of this legislation is:To redirect funding from nuclear weapons programs once thepresident certifies to Congress that all countries possessingnuclear weapons have begun the verifiable and irreversibleelimination of such weapons under the Treaty on theProhibition of Nuclear Weapons.[Page H1911]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
